== Extracted Lists

 The list environments below are extracted from arXiv LaTeX source and wrapped for pdfLaTeX validation.

  +  Conformal symmetry must underlie our mathematical description of nature.
  +  Naive conformal gravity fails.

  +  Scale changes, generated by the dilation operator, $D $ directly produce the allowed choices of units by rescaling lengths locally.
  +  Conformal translations. The four generators, $K_(a)$, translate infinitesimal vectors in inverse coordinates. Such a vector is inverted through a unit sphere, translated, then re-inverted. The transformation clearly involves an arbitrary displacement vector. The thing to notice -- or rather not to notice -- is that the vector is also rotated and rescaled. Since both rotating and stretching are already independent transformations, the group closes.

